If you have ANY questions on these rules or examples, please email me. If you have questions regarding a specific situation, email me and I&#146;ll give you a ruling. If you&#146;ve got some &quot;secret tech&quot; you don&#146;t want other players / teams to know about ahead of time, email me privately and I&#146;ll let you know; I&#146;m not playing, so you don&#146;t have to worry about me protecting myself from your ideas. I really can&#146;t stress this enough: If you have ANY concerns or questions about this document, contact me at BlackViper@mindspring.com so you can construct tournament worthy decks. I&#146;m looking forward to seeing you there! </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2"><a href="articles.php3"><img src="images/aback.GIF" border="0"></a><A HREF="articleread.php3?article=2277"><IMG SRC="images/aread.GIF" BORDER=0></A><A HREF="articlereview.php3?article=2277"><IMG SRC="images/areview.GIF" BORDER=0></A><a href="articleprint.php3?article=2277" TARGET="BLANK_"><img src="images/aprint.gif" border="0"></a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE> </td>
